Description: Green glazed composition scarab, elytra not marked but humeral callosities present, pierced longitudinally, base plain.
Excavator/field collector: Excavated by: Sir William Matthew Flinders Petrie
Bibliographic references: Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.66, p.181, pl.23)
